            Prime Minister Theresa May wins Tory confidence vote
            Sir Graham Brady, chairman of the 1922 Committee, has announced that Prime Minister Theresa May has retained the Conservative Party leadership, winning a confidence vote triggered by rebel MPs.She won by 200 votes to 117, comfortably clearing the threshold of 159 votes required to stave off a leadership contest. 
                
                        12 Dec 2018
                    
                
        
